CS:APP Shell Lab
=================

This repository contains the tiny shell (`tsh`) for the CS:APP Shell Lab.
The student implementation lives in `tsh.c`; the parser and job-list helpers
are provided in `tsh_helper.{c,h}`.

Repository layout
-----------------

- `tsh.c`: shell entry point, command execution, job control, and signal
  handling.
- `tsh_helper.{c,h}`: provided command parser and job-table utilities.
- `csapp.{c,h}`: CS:APP support library.
- `runtrace.c`, `wrapper.c`: driver and trace support.
- `traces/`: official trace files used to validate the shell.
- `testprogs/`: helper programs launched by the traces.

Build and cleanup
-----------------

- `make`: build `tsh`, `runtrace`, and the helper programs.
- `make clean`: remove generated binaries, objects, and temporary files.
- `make handin`: create `tshlab-handin.tar` with the required hand-in files.

Formatting
----------

- `make check-format`: verify the required formatting for `tsh.c`.
- `make format`: apply the repository formatting rules to `tsh.c`.

Run and verify
--------------

- `./tsh`: start the shell interactively.
- `./sdriver 2 -s ./tsh`: run the official driver against `trace02.txt`.

Current shell behavior
----------------------

The implementation in `tsh.c` currently covers:

- prompt display and EOF exit
- `quit`
- foreground and background jobs
- `jobs`
- `bg` and `fg` with PID or `%JID`
- `SIGCHLD`, `SIGINT`, and `SIGTSTP` handling
- `<` and `>` redirection for external commands
- `jobs > file`

Reproducible checks in this repo
--------------------------------

The commands below are the concrete checks that can be reproduced locally in
this repository:

- `make`
- `make check-format`
- `./sdriver 2 -s ./tsh`

Notes
-----

- `trace10` is not part of the active trace set in this repo.
- Generated files such as `*.o`, `tsh`, `runtrace`, and `tshlab-handin.tar`
  are build outputs and should not be committed.
